.TH MAN_1_SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "April 2024" "Version 1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple command-line shell program

.SH SYNOPSIS
simple_shell

.SH DESCRIPTION
simple_shell is a basic command-line shell program that allows users to interact with their operating system by executing commands. It provides a simple interface for running commands and scripts.

.SH OPTIONS
The simple_shell program does not accept any command-line options or arguments.

.SH USAGE
To use simple_shell, simply run the program from your command-line interface. Once launched, you will be presented with a prompt where you can enter commands. Press Enter after typing each command to execute it.

.SH EXAMPLES
To list files in the current directory:
.PP
.BR $ ls

To change directory to the parent directory:
.PP
.BR $ cd ..

.SH EXIT STATUS
simple_shell returns 0 upon successful execution of a command. If an error occurs during command execution, a non-zero exit status may be returned.

